Trazodone, an atypical antidepressant and serotonin receptor antagonist, can sometimes cause priapism, though this is rare. Other drugs in this category include nefazodone, mirtazapine, and mianserin. Trazodone is commonly used at low doses (50-200 mg) either alone or in combination with SSRIs or SNRIs to treat insomnia. In cases of priapism, treatment may involve the intracarvenous injection of phenylephrine.<br />
<br />
&nbsp;
<p><i><b>Reference</b>: Goodman &amp; Gillman&rsquo;s The Pharmacological Basis of Therapeutics, 14th edition, Page no 347,352 .</i></p>
<br />
&nbsp;

SRY region is present on the short arm of the Y chromosome(Yp11). SRY stands for the sex-determining region on Y. It contains the SRY gene, which produces the protein called the testis determining factor. This causes the gonads to develop into the testes. If the SRY gene or Y chromosome is absent, the gonads develop as ovaries.<br />
<br />
&nbsp;
<p><i><b>Reference</b>: Williams Gynaecology, 4th edition, Page no 408 .</i></p>
<br />
